DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numeric identifier for the results of the scientific determination of the presence and nature of disease used to classify a biologic material sample taken from a human.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._The investigation, analysis and recognition of the presence and nature of disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms; also, the scientific determination of any kind; the concise results of such an investigation._One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.
